# BOTSPEAK Versioning Protocol [ALWAYS]

[ALWAYS] this rule applies to ALL edits to SPEC.md · skills/botspeak/SKILL.md · installed skill copies

## version sources of truth

[REFERENCE] SPEC.md line 1   = `# BOTSPEAK SPEC vX.Y.Z`  (the authoritative version)
[REFERENCE] SPEC.md line 3   = `<!-- botspeak-version: X.Y.Z · published: YYYY-MM-DD · repo: ... -->`
[REFERENCE] SKILL.md line 6  = `<!-- botspeak-version: X.Y.Z · published: YYYY-MM-DD · repo: ... -->`
[REFERENCE] SKILL.md step 7  = hardcoded format string `<!-- BOTSPEAK vX.Y.Z · compressed by [model] · YYYY-MM-DD -->`

[ALWAYS] all four locations MUST agree · !! mismatch -> treat as broken version

## when to bump SPEC.md version

[REFERENCE] PATCH (X.Y.Z -> X.Y.Z+1)  clarification · wording fix · new example · no new rules or symbols
[REFERENCE] MINOR (X.Y.Z -> X.Y+1.0)  new section · new symbol · new phase tag · backward-compatible rule change
[REFERENCE] MAJOR (X.Y.Z -> X+1.0.0)  complete overhaul · breaking symbol contract · new paradigm

[ON-TRIGGER] any edit to SPEC.md -> bump version in H1 + metadata comment · !! even for typo fixes

## skill publish protocol

[ON-TRIGGER] user says "publish skill" || "release skill" || "update the installed skill" || "distill spec to skill":

### pre-flight
  confirm SPEC.md version is finalized · !! stop if SPEC.md has uncommitted edits that haven't been version-bumped
  ask user (prose) for a short-tag describing what changed (e.g. "versioning-header", "strict-equals-rule", "conflict-detection")
  if user does not provide one -> infer from the largest change in SPEC.md since last skill version

### step 1 — determine archive seq
  read skills/_archive/README.md
  find the highest existing seq number in the botspeak/ table (e.g. v07 -> next = 08)
  pad to 2 digits

### step 2 — write the new skill
  distill SPEC.md -> skills/botspeak/SKILL.md (or apply targeted edits if partial update)
  update version comment (line after frontmatter ---): `<!-- botspeak-version: X.Y.Z · published: YYYY-MM-DD · repo: https://github.com/itaki/botspeak -->`
  update step 7 hardcoded format string: `<!-- BOTSPEAK vX.Y.Z · compressed by [model] · YYYY-MM-DD -->`
  !! SKILL.md version MUST equal SPEC.md version before continuing

### step 3 — archive the new skill + SPEC
  count lines in skills/botspeak/SKILL.md
  archive filename: `v<seq>-<YYYYMMDD>-<lines>L-<short-tag>.md`
  cp skills/botspeak/SKILL.md skills/_archive/botspeak/<filename>
  count lines in SPEC.md
  spec archive seq = highest existing seq in skills/_archive/spec/ + 1
  cp SPEC.md skills/_archive/spec/v<seq>-<YYYYMMDD>-<lines>L-<short-tag>.md

### step 4 — install
  cp skills/botspeak/SKILL.md ~/.cursor/skills-cursor/botspeak/SKILL.md

### step 5 — update archive README
  add row to the botspeak/ table in skills/_archive/README.md:
    | v<seq> | YYYY-MM-DD | <lines> | `<git-short-hash>` | <short-tag> + key changes (1 sentence) |
  add row to the spec/ table in skills/_archive/README.md (same format)
  get git short hash: `git rev-parse --short HEAD` (use `pending` if not yet committed)

### step 6 — confirm
  tell user (prose):
    "Published BOTSPEAK v<X.Y.Z> as archive v<seq> (<lines> lines, <short-tag>).
     Installed to ~/.cursor/skills-cursor/botspeak/SKILL.md.
     Archive entry added to skills/_archive/README.md."

!! do NOT publish if SPEC.md and SKILL.md versions differ
!! do NOT skip the archive step — the archive is the regression test baseline

## sync check

[ON-TRIGGER] user asks "what version is botspeak?" || "is the skill up to date?":
  read SPEC.md line 1 + line 3
  read skills/botspeak/SKILL.md line 6 + step 7 format string
  read ~/.cursor/skills-cursor/botspeak/SKILL.md line 6
  report (prose): SPEC version · SKILL version · installed version · all match? yes/no

[ALWAYS] !! never edit SKILL.md version without also editing SPEC.md version
[ALWAYS] !! never ship a compressed output with a version string that doesn't match the skill that ran
